abstract: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state trying to fire up voters and make a last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state trying to fire up voters and make a last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.

abstract: He also recalled an argument Hillary Clinton made in 2016 that didn’t work out.
snippet: He also recalled an argument Hillary Clinton made in 2016 that didn’t work out.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Pacing the stage Saturday evening in an overflowing hotel ballroom in Des Moines, Andrew Yang reeled off a familiar array of facts and figures, including the decline of Americans’ life expectancy, the millions of trucking and retail jobs vulnerable to automation and the zero dollars Amazon pays in federal taxes. But it was an unknown data set that quickly stirred up his crowd.

abstract: Hiram Monserrate, the first member of New York’s Legislature to be expelled in nearly a century, is running again.
snippet: Hiram Monserrate, the first member of New York’s Legislature to be expelled in nearly a century, is running again.
lead_paragraph: For the better part of a decade, the name Hiram Monserrate has been shorthand for the darkest side of New York politics.

abstract: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
snippet: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
headline_main: In Iowa, Anxiety and Unpredictability Clouds Caucus Finish
headline_print_headline: In Iowa, Anxiety and Unpredictability Clouds Caucus Finish

abstract: The release of the highly anticipated survey was canceled after Pete Buttigieg’s campaign raised concerns that he was not included in at least one phone call.
snippet: The release of the highly anticipated survey was canceled after Pete Buttigieg’s campaign raised concerns that he was not included in at least one phone call.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A highly anticipated poll of Iowa Democrats, set to be released two days before the presidential caucuses, was shelved on Saturday night because of concerns about irregularities in the methodology.

abstract: The United Kingdom finally cast off from the European Union on Friday for an uncertain future, with Brexiteers claiming victory and popping champagne corks for an "independence day" they said marked a new era for the country.
snippet: The United Kingdom finally cast off from the European Union on Friday for an uncertain future, with Brexiteers claiming victory and popping champagne corks for an "independence day" they said marked a new era for the country.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The United Kingdom finally cast off from the European Union on Friday for an uncertain future, with Brexiteers claiming victory and popping champagne corks for an "independence day" they said marked a new era for the country.
headline_main: Brexit at Last: Britain Leaves the EU as Champagne Corks Fly
headline_print_headline: Brexit at Last: Britain Leaves the EU as Champagne Corks Fly

abstract: “You could tell by listening to Gang of Four music that punk had happened,” he once said. “But it definitely wasn’t punk music.”
snippet: “You could tell by listening to Gang of Four music that punk had happened,” he once said. “But it definitely wasn’t punk music.”
lead_paragraph: Andy Gill, whose slashing, dissonant guitar playing in Gang of Four inspired waves of post-punk to come, died on Saturday in London. He was 64.
